.7, "y1": 42.2}, {"x0": 9.1, "y0": 64.08, "x1": 90.69, "y1": 88.29}], "full_text": "Radiology\nHydropneumothorax\nHemothorax\n• Hemothorax occurs in approximately one-third of patients with thoracic trauma,\noften in combination with pneumothorax.\n• Signs of hemothorax at radiography include:\n1. blunting of the costophrenic angle\n2. obscuration of the hemidiaphragm\n3. homogeneous opacity of the hemithorax\n4. fluid within the interlobar fissures.\n75"}